def: Two-nerved; -- applied to leaves which have two longitudinalribs or nerves.
Of or pertaining to Ionia or the Ionians; Ionic.-- n.
Free from bias or prejudice; unprejudiced; impartial.-- Un*bi"ased*ness, n.
To plunder; to pillage; to despoil; to rob.
Separated from its trunk or stock. [Obs.]
To thicken. [R.]The nightmare Life-in-death was she, Who thicks man's blood withcold. Coleridge.
Pertaining to written evidence; contained or certified inwriting. "Documentary evidence." Macaulay.
